      "special": false,
      "stages": null,
      "description": "The Church is called The Original Sin as a reminder that all of its members are sinners in some way or another. The Original Sin is open to everyone regardless of their past which is why most of the Congregation members are \"innocence-impaired\". The saloon doors are meant to symbolize that \"the door is always open\" for anyone to join. However, it is this same open-door policy that doomed them.",
